Work as European Solidarity Corps volunteer in Denmark
  URL: https://www.afs.dk/frivillig-udlandet/evs-hosting-opportunities-in-denmark/
  Work in interesting Danish volunteering projects as an European Solidarity Corps volunteer in Denmark through AFS Interkultur.

  --- Content ---
  ![](https://d22dvihj4pfop3.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/54/2022/05/10125724/ESC-logo.png)
  
  AFS Interkultur is a Lead Organization in the European Solidarity Corps. We work together with some great projects and help them with the recruitment process of new volunteers.
  
  **Who can apply?** You can apply if you are between 18 and 30 years old.
  
  You have to be a resident in one of the following countries, which are a part of the program: Albania, Algeria, Armenia, Austria, Azerbaijan, Belarus, Belgium, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus, Egypt, Estonia, Finland , France, Georgia, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Iceland, Israel, Italy, Jordan, Kosovo, Latvia, Lebanon, Libya, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Morocco, Moldova, Montenegro, Netherlands, North Macedonia, Norway, Palestine, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Syria, The Czech Republic, Tunisia, Turkey, and Ukraine.
  
  **As a general rule you can only participate in an ESC project once, however there are circumstances in which applicants can be considered for a second project. If you are unsure if you can apply, contact us.**
  
  **How can I apply?** On this page you can read more about the different projects, you can see which projects are actively recruiting and **how to apply.**
  
  Please make sure to read the whole description of the project and about how to apply. You find the link for the **online application form** under each project. Each project has its own link. You can apply to as many projects as you would like.
  
  Please do not contact the projects directly. If you have any questions about the application process or the project please forward them to evs-denmark@afs.org. We are in AFS handling the recruitment process.
  
  Be aware that we do not receive applications by email. If you do send us one it will not be taken into consideration. You have to apply online.
  
  ![](https://d22dvihj4pfop3.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/54/2021/05/19135950/DA-Funded-by-the-EU_POS-300x60.jpg)
  
  ### Om organisationen / About the organisation
  
  _English below_
  
  AFS Interkultur er en NGO, der arbejder for fred og mellemfolkelig forståelse gennem udvekslings- og volontørophold i det meste af verden. Vi sender og modtager hvert år omkring 500 udvekslingsstuderende og volontører, der ønsker at lære sig selv og verden at kende gennem personlige kulturmøder. I Danmark har AFS Interkultur omkring 30 lokalforeninger, der drives af 450 aktive frivillige. Vi er ca. 20 ansatte på det danske sekretariat, der ligger på Frederiksberg.
  
  I AFS tror vi på, at interkulturel forståelse og møder på tværs af forskelle skaber solidaritet. Vi tror på, at vi gennem mødet med hinandens kulturelle forskelle kan blive mere opmærksom på vores egen kultur, skabe dybere forståelse, mere sympati og færre fordomme, og vores aktivitet tager udgangspunkt i de overbevisninger.
  
  I mere end 50 år har AFS Interkultur arrangeret udvekslinger med næsten 50 forskellige lande. Vi har ekstensiv erfaring i interkulturel læring og kompetencer og har et bredt dækkende frivillignetværk over Danmark til at sikre effektiv understøttelse af alle deltageres ophold i Danmark. AFS Interkultur har taget del i det Europæiske Solidaritetskorps (førhen EVS) siden 1997 som både en værts, sende og koordinerende organisation.
  
  AFS-programmer inkluderer
  
  - High School ophold for unge mellem 15 og 18 år (vi modtager både internationale unge i Danmark og sender unge danskere ud i verden)
  - Programmer for unge voksne over 18, der ønsker at tage et semester eller to ved et universitet i udlandet
  - Programmer for unge voksne over 18, der ønsker at lave frivilligt arbejde i Europa, Afrika, Asien, Centralamerika, Sydamerika og Australien (her modtager vi både til Danmark og sender unge danskere ud i verden).
  
  Organisationens OID nummer: E10021588
  
  **AFS Interkultur** is a partner in the worldwide youth exchange organisation, American Field Service, represented in over 55 countries all over the world. AFS is a voluntary based, non-profit NGO, independent of political and religious interests. In Denmark, AFS started in 1957 and is today the oldest and largest non-profit exchange organisation in Denmark with 20 staff members, more than 30 local chapters (including Greenland and the Faroe Island) and more than 2.000 members, many of whom work as volunteers for the organisation.
  
  In AFS, we believe that through intercultural understanding and by creating meetings across differences we create solidarity among us. We believe that by getting to know each other’s differences and by becoming aware of our own culture we can create more understanding, more sympathy and less prejudices. Those thoughts are at the foundation for all of our activities.
  
  For more than 50 years, AFS Interkultur has organised exchanges between almost 50 countries of the world. We have extensive experience in intercultural learning and a network throughout the country to ensure proper support to all participants hosted in Denmark. AFS Interkultur has been involved with the European Solidarity Corps (previous EVS) programme since 1997 both as a sending, hosting and coordinating organisation.
  
  AFS’s programmes include:
  
  - High school stay abroad for young people between 15-18 years (hosting and sending)
  - Programmes for people above the age of 18 spending their gap year taking one or two semesters at a college or university abroad
  - Programmes for people above the age of 18 doing voluntary work in Europe, Africa, Asia, Central America, South America and Australia (hosting and sending)
  
  AFS Interkultur has two volunteer committees that are a core part of the organisational structure. These committees are responsible for camps and trainings of those that choose to travel with AFS, whether they depart from or arrive to Denmark.
  
  The organisation’s OID number: E10021588
  
  ### Aktivitetsperiode / Activity period
  
  Vi forestiller os, at du kan starte d. 1. august 2026 og at du kan være her i 12 måneder.
  
  Men vi vil gerne tale med dig hvis 6 måneder passer dig bedre, eller hvis en senere startdato passer bedre.
  
  We imagine that you can start August 1st, 2026, and that you will stay for 12 months. But we are also open to discussing a shorter period or later start time.
  
  ### Aktivitetsbeskrivelse / Activity descption
  
  _English below_
  
  **_Vil du være med til at få flere unge fra Grønland ud i verden – og sikre, at de lander godt, når de kommer afsted?_**
  
  AFS Interkultur søger en ESC-volontør til programafdelingen med fokus på vores arbejde med grønlandske deltagere.
  
  I rollen bliver du en del af arbejdet med at rekruttere, forberede og følge op på unge fra Grønland, som tager på udveksling. Du kommer til at arbejde tæt sammen med både ansatte, frivillige og vores lokalforening i Grønland – og du vil være med til at drive en række processer, som er vigtige for, at deltagerne har nogle gode ophold.
  
  **Hvad du kommer til at lave**
  
  Du bliver involveret i hele “maskinrummet” omkring vores grønlandske deltagere.
  
  Du kan for eksempel komme til at arbejde med følgende:
  
  _Rekruttering og informationsarbejde_
  
  - Planlægge og afholde informationsmøder for unge i Grønland, der overvejer et AFS-ophold
  - Være i dialog med potentielle deltagere og deres familier
  - Samarbejde tæt med lokalforeningen i Grønland om at nå ud til nye ansøgere
  
  _Interviews og udvælgelse_
  
  - Støtte op om lokalforeningen og frivillige i Grønland i forbindelse med interviews og udvælgelse af deltagere
  
  _Ansøgnings- og visumprocesser_
  
  - Hjælpe deltagere med deres ansøgninger
  - Understøtte arbejdet med dokumenter, deadlines og krav
  - Bidrage til koordinering af visum og administrative processer
  - Arbejde tæt sammen med både frivillige og sekretariatet om at få alle brikker til at falde på plads
  
  _Opfølgning under ophold_
  
  - Planlægge og deltage i online informations- og forberedelsesforløb for deltagere og deres forældre
  - Facilitere online opfølgningssessioner (evt. på grønlandsk) for deltagere under ophold med fokus på trivsel og erfaringsdeling
  - Bidrage til planlægning og gennemførelse af forberedende aktiviteter, herunder evt. deltagelse i lejr i Nuuk
  
  _Tværgående opgaver_
  
  - Bidrage til at styrke forståelsen for grønlandske deltagere og kontekst i samarbejdet med medarbejdere og frivillige
  - Oversætte og tilpasse kommunikation mellem dansk og grønlandsk i dialog med deltagere og deres familier
  
  **Det du bidrager til**
  
  - at flere unge fra Grønland får mulighed for at tage på udveksling
  - at de er godt forberedte, når de rejser ud
  - at de bliver fulgt op undervejs i deres ophold
  - at samarbejdet mellem frivillige, lokalforening og sekretariat fungerer i praksis
  
  _**Would you like to help more young people from Greenland explore the world?**_
  
  AFS Intercultural Programs is looking for an ESC volunteer for the program department, with a focus on our work with Greenlandic participants.
  
  In this role, you will be part of recruiting, preparing, and following up with young people from Greenland who go on exchange programs. You will work closely with staff, volunteers, and our local AFS Chapters in Greenland, and you will help drive a number of processes that ensure participants have a positive experience during their exchange stay.
  
  **What you will be doing** You will be involved across different phases for our Greenlandic participants.
  
  For example, you may work with:
  
  _Recruitment and information activities_
  
  - Plan and facilitate information sessions for young people in Greenland who are considering an AFS exchange
  - Communicate with prospective participants and their families
  - Collaborate and support the local chapters in Greenland to reach new applicants
  
  _Interviews and selection_
  
  - Support the local chapter and volunteers in Greenland with participant selection
  
  _Application and visa processes_
  
  - Assist participants with their applications
  - Support work related to documents, deadlines, and requirements
  - Contribute to coordinating visa and administrative processes
  - Work closely with both volunteers and the secretariat to ensure everything falls into place
  
  _Follow-up during the stay_
  
  - Plan and take part in online information and preparation sessions for participants and their parents
  - Facilitate online follow-up sessions (possibly in Greenlandic) for participants during their stay, focusing on their well-being and sharing of experiences
  - Contribute to planning and implementing preparatory activities, including possible participation in a camp in Nuuk
  
  _Other tasks_
  
  - Help strengthen understanding of Greenlandic participants and their context in collaboration with staff and volunteers
  - Translate and adapt communication between Danish and Greenlandic in dialogue with participants and their families
  
  **What you contribute to**
  
  - More young people from Greenland gaining the opportunity to go on exchange
  - Ensuring they are well prepared before departure
  - Ensuring they are supported throughout their stay
  - Ensuring effective collaboration between volunteers, the local organization, and the secretariat in practice
  
  ### Profil / Profile
  
  _English below_
  
  **Vi forventer, at du**
  
  - er mellem 18 og 30 år (krav i ESC-programmet)
  - taler grønlandsk og kan begå dig på dansk
  - har lyst til at arbejde med unge mennesker og kulturmøder
  - trives i en rolle med mange bolde i luften og flere parallelle opgaver
  - har lyst til både at tage kontakt, facilitere og arbejde med konkrete processer
  
  Det er en fordel, men ikke et krav, hvis du:
  
  - taler engelsk
  - selv har været på udveksling, har boet i udlandet eller på anden vis har erfaring med kulturmøder
  
  Vi kan se muligheder i mange forskellige uddannelsesbaggrunde, så det har ingen betydning hvad du læser eller planlægger at læse, men stillingen kan **ikke** indgå som en del af din uddannelse.
  
  **We expect that**
  
  - You are between 18 and 30 years old
  - You speak Greenlandic and some Danish
  - You have an interest in cultural meetings
  - You enjoy meeting new people
  - You wish to work with young people
  - You are currently living in Greenland, or are a Greenlandic individual living in Denmark
  
  It will be an advantage, but not a must, if you
  
  - Are comfortable in English
  - Have been on an international exchange, lived abroad or have other personal experience with intercultural encounters
  
  We can see many advantages and opportunities in a variety of educational backgrounds, so it is less important what you are studying or have studied, however, this position **cannot** be part of your studies.
  
  ### Hvad får du ud af det? / What do you get?
  
  _English below_
  
  European Solidarity Corps er et EU-finansieret frivilligprogram, som også er et læringsprogram for dig.
  
  Som ESC-volontør i AFS bliver du en del af en international organisation og får erfaring med:
  
  - at arbejde med rekruttering, interviews og deltagerforløb
  - at koordinere komplekse processer med mange involverede
  - at facilitere møder og aktiviteter for unge
  - at arbejde i et internationalt og interkulturelt miljø
  
  Derudover får du:
  
  - en personlig mentor
  - adgang til ESC-kurser og [YouthPass](https://www.youthpass.eu/en/)
  - Kursus i interkulturel læring [Global Up Abroad](https://www.globalup.com/)
  - et internationalt fællesskab af andre ESC-volontører i Danmark
  - en arbejdsplads på AFS’ sekretariat på Frederiksberg
  
  **The European Solidarity Corps** is an EU-funded volunteering program that also serves as a learning experience for you.
  
  As an ESC volunteer at AFS, you will become part of an international organization and gain experience in:
  
  - working with recruitment, interviews, and participant processes
  - coordinating complex processes involving many stakeholders
  - facilitating meetings and activities for young people
  - working in an international and intercultural environment
  
  You will also get:
  
  - A personal mentor throughout your entire stay
  - A [YouthPass](https://www.youthpass.eu/en/) certificate
  - A course in intercultural learning –  [Global Up Abroad](https://www.globalup.com/)
  - Becoming a part of the international group of ESC’ers in Denmark
  - Becoming part of the large AFS family
  
  ### Praktisk/Practicalities
  
  _English below_
  
  Du vil arbejde på vores kontor i København. Vi er placeret cirka 3,5 km fra byens centrum. Den forventede arbejdstid er omkring 37 timer om ugen. Der vil lejlighedsvis også være aften- og weekendarbejde. Timer, der arbejdes uden for normal arbejdstid, kan afspadseres på andre tidspunkter. Du kommer til at optjene to feriedage om måneden.
  
  AFS vil være ansvarlig for at finde bolig til volontøren. Det forventes, at volontøren indkvarteres i et enkeltværelse i [CPH Village](https://www.cphvillage.com/norrebro).
  
  Som en del af European Solidarity Corps-programmet dækker vi følgende:
  
  - International transport dækkes op til et vist beløb. EU fastsætter et budget afhængigt af afstanden til vores kontor. Hvis du rejser grønt, vil dit budget være højere
  - Sundhedsforsikring
  - Kost og logi
  - Lommepenge/ydelse: 380 euro om måneden i alt: 360 euro (fastsat af EU) + 20 euro fra den lokale AFS-afdeling
  - Daglig transport fra CPH Village til AFS kontor dækkes.
  
  **You will be** working at our office in Copenhagen. We are located approximately 3.5 km from the city centre. You should expect to work approximately 37 hours a week. There will occasionally be evening/weekend work as well. The hours done outside office hours can be taken off at other times. The volunteer will receive two vacation days per month.
  
  AFS will be responsible for finding accommodation for the volunteer. It is expected that the volunteer will be accommodated in a single room in [CPH Village](https://www.cphvillage.com/norrebro) .
  
  As a part of the European Solidarity Corps program, the following is covered by us:
  
  - International transport is covered to a certain amount. The EU sets a budget depending on the distance to our office. If you travel in a green way your budget will be higher!
  - Health insurance
  - Food and accommodation
