  ### About the organisation
  
  Halvorsminde Efterskole & Fri Fagskole is a self-governing Danish educational institution. We operate on government grants and student fees and are part of the Danish Efterskole and Fri Fagskole traditions.
  
  Halvorsminde offers a unique combination of general and vocational education for young students aged 14 to 18 years. Our students live at the school, sharing both study and everyday life in a close and active community.
  
  The school has two educational branches:
  
  - Halvorsminde Efterskole offering 9th and 10th grade programmes focusing on academic subjects, sports, creativity and personal development.
  - Halvor Fri Fagskole offering practice-oriented study lines such as Crafts & Design (Kloge Hænder), Gastronomy & Bakery, Style & Wellness, and Business & Event.
  
  Halvorsminde follows the Grundtvigian philosophy, emphasizing openness, equality, responsibility and community. Everyday life combines academic learning, craftsmanship, creativity, sports and movement – all rooted in personal growth, fellowship and active participation.
  
  We are a community of around 140 students and 30 staff members – teachers, trainees, visiting professionals and volunteers – all contributing to the unique Halvorsminde atmosphere.
  
  To learn more, please visit our website: [www.halvorsminde.dk](http://www.halvorsminde.dk/)
  
