  ### Activity description
  
  At Kalø Økologiske Landbrugsskole, volunteers in the kitchen will engage in a dynamic program centered around sustainable food systems. The kitchen prepares daily meals for 80-125 people, using organic produce from the school’s farm. Volunteers will assist in meal preparation, food preservation (e.g., pickling, freezing, and drying surplus produce), menu planning, and maintaining a clean and organized kitchen environment. This role emphasizes sustainability, minimizing food waste, and promoting farm-to-table practices.
  
  In general, the volunteer will gain hands-on experience in sustainable kitchen operations, learn about organic food production, and explore how local, seasonal ingredients are integrated into nutritious meals. Volunteers will also have the opportunity to share their own cultural food traditions and recipes, enriching the school’s culinary offerings. While kitchen activities follow a structured schedule, volunteers may occasionally participate in events or activities outside normal hours, with compensatory time off provided.
  
  The volunteer will live at the school alongside the students and be encouraged to integrate into the vibrant community life. The school offers a wide range of student-driven social activities and facilities, including choir, a fitness room, table tennis, pool, and football. The beautiful surroundings invite you to explore the nearby forest, bike or walk in nature, and even take a swim in the ocean. Aarhus, Denmark’s second-largest city, is also easily accessible and offers abundant cultural and leisure opportunities.
  
  ### Volunteer profile
  
  The recruitment process is open to all, but it is preferred that the volunteer has a keen interest in learning about sustainable food systems, organic cooking, and reducing food waste. We will highly value a volunteer who enjoys working in a kitchen environment and is enthusiastic about preparing meals, preserving produce, and contributing to the farm-to-table cycle. A willingness to collaborate, try new things, and bring their own cultural food traditions to the table will be greatly appreciated.
  
  _NB. This activity may ultimately be a mixed farming & kitchen position. Thus, applicants must be ready for that. This will be clearly communicated in good time._
  
