  ### About the organisation
  
  [Ungdomshøjskolen ved Ribe](http://www.uhr.dk/)  – The Youth Folk High School at Ribe – from here on noted as UHR – is a traditional Danish folk high school, where young people between 16 and 19 years stay to learn democracy in practice, strengthen social abilities and develop skills in subjects like sports, outdoor life, design, art, media, music, drama, journalism, sustainability, and cooking. At classes – and everywhere else – we speak a combination of Danish and English.
  
  As a folk high school, we operate on the main aims: life information, public information, and democratic formation. The values of the school are open mindedness, human respect, responsibility, and community in a safe environment. The students are her on voluntary basis for either one or two semesters, the classes are mandatory, but there are no tests or exams. Our students typically come here between primary school and youth education, to work with subjects of interest and to prepare themselves for their further education. For our international students, and our volunteers, we have the subject Danish, where Danish
  
  language and culture is taught.
  
  UHR is an international school, where young people from around the world come to stay. Between one third and half of our students are international. International and Danish students live together in one of our four student houses. All students live at the school in double or single rooms. All students help with practical tasks, such as cleaning and kitchen duties. All teachers live in houses around UHR, which gives a very special and safe, homely environment.
  
  UHR is situated in the middle of the beautiful village Vester Vedsted, just 7 km south of Ribe, and right next to the Wadden sea.
  
  The organisations OID number: E10213884
  
  ### Activity period
  
  1st August 2026 –  30th June 2027
  
  (The exact length of the mobility is depending on the funding from the EU commission).
  
  ### Activity description
  
  Being a volunteer at our højskole, means that you become part of a small, strong community, where students and staff live and work together. The one or two volunteers are invited into the planning process, for them to put their personal stamp on activities in classes and other areas. The planning will be made together with the volunteers either ahead of, or at the very beginning of their stay. The volunteers are also involved in the practical and pedagogical processes at UHR, why they will participate in the weekly staff meetings. Further, the volunteers will take part in the work with the contact groups. Another important aspect of the volunteers’ integration and connection to the students and teachers at the UHR are the meals which the volunteers will have together with the staff and students.
  
  Typical tasks at UHR will, on one hand, be practical work with office, caretaker, kitchen, cleaning, or teaching. On the other hand, it will be of pedagogical character in relation to language classes, sports classes, or creative classes. Evening activities, classes and events for the students can be arranged by the volunteers in corporation with the staff. The volunteers will have a weekly evening at work, either by socializing or making activities with or classes for the students.
  
  Volunteering work can take place on weekdays as well as in weekends.
  
  As a volunteer you will have a personal mentor. Volunteers assist the teachers on the two study trips in Autumn and in Spring.
  
  Christmas holiday is from 19/12 2026 till 5/1 2027, where the school is closed. Volunteers can stay at the school during the vacation, but there are no meals at the school.
  
  Accommodation is in a small apartment on campus, in single rooms. The apartment is shared with the other volunteer. All meals are served in the school’s dining room.
  
  ### Volunteer profile
  
  The following criteria would be preferable:
  
  - The students at UHR are between 16 and 19 years, so volunteers around mid- twenties to thirty will be preferred.
  - Volunteers that can contribute in areas such as teaching, kitchen, office, cleaning and handiwork will be preferred.
  - English speaking volunteers will be preferred.
  
  ### Practicalities
  
  The volunteers are lodged at the Youth folk high school’s grounds in a small apartment. Each
  
  volunteer has their own room and share a living room, bathroom and small kitchen. All meals will
  
  be provided by the school in the dining room together with the students and the staff.
  
