  ### About the organisation
  
  Volunteer at Kulturfabrikken: a place where the local children and young people can go and participate in events, concerts, workshops or skate, climb or just hang out in the café with their friends. A place to which they can belong, where they can be themselves.
  
  The values of Kulturfabrikken are, among others: competence, voluntariness, involvement, trust, respect, broadmindedness, dialogue, sustainability and climate awareness.
  
  **Some of our regular activities:**
  
  _Visual arts and creative activities, i.e.:_
  
  - Visual arts education for children from 6-15 years in their spare time. At present, 3 classes.
  - Visual arts courses for all Year 1 children. Approx. 30 courses a year.
  - Spontaneous creative activities in the café for daily users.
  - Open creative workshop once a week for everyone between 10 and 30 years.
  - Design workshop once a week for everyone between 10 and 30 years.
  
  _Concerts:_ 1-2 “adult” concerts a month and 12-14 concerts a year for children and their families.
  
  _Volunteer Crew:_ An active and engaged volunteer crew, they develop events, select bands, and take practical part in events/activities.
  
  _Food Community:_ We have previously cooperated with “Madfællesskab Lolland-Falster”, a local organisation under “the food community”, anchored with the Danish Ministry of Food. Healthy, delicious and cheap food, with food waste and a sustainable food system in focus. We have held several food events; we cook and eat together. Healthy and sustainable food is one of our focus areas.
  
  _Skate and Climbing Hall:_ One of Denmark’s best skate halls, we cooperate with the local skate association about running it. Bouldering climbing cave and two climbing walls, run by the climbing association.
  
  _The Café:_ The heart of Kulturfabrikken. Here young people hang out, meet friends and deal with all that happens in their lives. It is often here that the volunteers and the young people establish ties. The volunteers go to language school and often get help from the users to do their Danish homework, and the users train their English, as most communication is in English. We are open Monday-Thursday 15.00.18.00 and 12.00-15.00 in the holidays.
  
  Kulturfabrikken also takes part in SSP, a cooperation between schools, social services and the police, working to create well-being and prevent crime among children and young people.
  
  **OID number:** E10094641
  
  ### Activity period
  
  From 15th September 2026 to 31st August 2027.
  
  (The exact length of the mobility is depending on the funding from the EU commission).
  
  ### Activity description
  
  At Kulturfabrikken, the volunteer will not only get to know the Danes but also meet another volunteer from another European country – in a house which has already had several volunteers from European countries – and in which a previous volunteer from Latvia is now working. Kulturfabrikken is a place where the local children and young people can go and participate in events, concerts, workshops, skate, climb or just hang out in the café with their friends. A place to which they can belong, where they can be themselves.
  
  To have volunteers in the house will benefit the volunteers, the users of the house and the members of staff. The volunteers contribute to the good atmosphere, with a different view, new ideas and an international outlook, which makes both users and staff take a fresh look at how we do things. Kulturfabrikken says: “Having volunteers in the house helps us to open our minds and renew ourselves. We have felt the difference in the periods when they were not here.”
  
  **Typically, the volunteers will be working at Kulturfabrikken with:**
  
  - Day-to-day running of the café; together with a member of staff or another volunteer
  - Participating in events; all stages from preparation to cleaning up, in cooperation with members of staff (especially at large events, all members of staff are involved)
  - Workshops during the holidays; sometimes a volunteer has a workshop of their own, sometimes they are practical helpers
  - Planning and participating in “Åbent Værksted” and “Designstuen” every week
  - Participating in the weekly team meeting with all staff
  - Participating in the weekly mentor meeting
  - Writing monthly blogs for Kulturfabrikken’s webpage
  - Document/take photos during events and workshops and upload to photo file
  - Language school, typically twice a week
  
  The list is not complete, there will always be other/new tasks, including projects which the volunteers start on their own.
  
  The volunteers work approx. 35 hours a week and we include the hours they go to language school, as working hours. There will be some work during evenings and weekends, as it is here, we hold many of our events and you should be prepared for long working days now and then.
  
  ### Volunteer profile
  
  The ideal volunteers are young people who want to work with children and young people, are creative performers themselves, passionate about live concerts and music and would like to work on their own projects within the framework offered by Kulturfabrikken.
  
  We value young people with an open and curious approach, a positive and optimistic outlook on life and a desire to work in a smaller organization where there are many different tasks to be solved.
  
  Volunteers should be ready to live with another volunteer and to take care of themselves.
  
