  ### Activity description
  
  At the beginning of the stay, there will be a start-up meeting between the volunteer, mentor, and the management of the school. Here the volunteer will be introduced to the school and its rules and regulations.
  
  We are looking for two volunteers within two different fields.
  
  1. SoMe, and marketing tasks: you will be working closely with the office and a couple of teachers responsible for the Social Media profiles and other platforms. We expect you to be part of special occasions, daily school life, and documenting fun and games. You will be equipped with a camera and a computer. Besides this, there will be a variety of tasks according to your skills and interests.
  2. Taking part in the practical tasks: you will be part of the kitchen team and get to work with the students. All the students take part in the kitchen work, and you will get a chance to connect with the students during the tasks. Besides that, you can be part of the outdoor team according to your skills and interests.
  
  Both volunteers will be part of the evening shifts and weekends. You will be asked to arrange social activities according to your skills and interests. Evening activities are about giving our students the oportunity to join different kinds of social activities to get involved with each other.
  
  Furthermore, events, weekend activities, and parties with the students can be arranged by the volunteers, in collaboration with the staff.
  
  Examples of activities: games night, outdoor activities, sports activities, music quizzes, walking, discussion clubs, etc. Some activities are mandatory – others optional.
  
  In some cases, it is possible for the volunteers to participate in the optional subjects, either as a teaching assistant or as a participant eg. Pottery, art, sewing, volleyball, handball, music etc.
  
  We expect you to learn Danish, ordinarily in language school and will plan your volunteer work according to the language school schedule.
  
