  AFS Interkultur will be the lead organisation of this project. That means that we will coordinate your stay and administer the ESC grant – including the volunteer allowance to be given.
  
  AFS Interkultur will assist volunteers with the administrative paperwork related to arriving in Denmark and will be an extra support during the stay next to the support organisation and the hosting organisation.
  
  ### About the organisation
  
  Ådum kindergarten is located near Skjern in the western part of Jutland. (the western part of Denmark).
  
  Ådum Kindergarten is located in the countryside area, and works closely with the local community.
  
  Ådum Kindergarden is a sport kindergarden, which means that we focus on movement and sports for the children on daily basis. We use our big playground every day and go for walks in our local area.
  
  In the kindergarden there are approx 60 children. 40 children in the kindergarden (age 3-6 years) and 20 children in the nursery (age 6 month-3 years)
  
  Ådum kindergarden is located close to the fjord and the North sea, where it is possible to practice wather sports.
  
  In the immediate area there is the opportunity to join different kinds of sports facilities, such as badminton, football, handball, fitness and swimming.
  
  For more information about Ådum Børnehave and Vuggestue click [HERE](https://www.afs.dk/frivillig-udlandet/evs-hosting-opportunities-in-denmark/aaudum.com)
  
  The organisation’s OID number: E10004278
  
  ### Activity period
  
  August 2023 to May 2024 (The exact length of the mobility is depending on the funding from the EU commission).
  
  ### Activity description
  
  In Ådum kindergarten the volunteer will learn how a kindergarten works in a small Danish community. Thus, the volunteer will participate in the activities which are planned, but also have the opportunity to plan other activities for smaller or bigger groups of children.
  
  Ådum kindergarten appreciates traditions and therefore celebrates birthdays, Christmas, Easter etc. Thus, the volunteer gets a great insight in the Danish traditions celebrated in a kindergarten.
  
  The volunteer will have a supervisor in the kindergarten, but he or she will also be a part of the regular staff.
  
  ### Volunteer profile
  
  Ådum kindergarten prefers a volunteer who has a background with child caring. And that the volunteer has the ability to interact with the children in a good and meaningful way. The volunteer should be interested in working with children, and interested in the development of children. The volunteer should be open minded and able to speak English on a conversational level.
  
  ### Practicalities
  
  The volunteer will either stay with a local Danish host family.
  
  In the host families the volunteer will be expected to become part of the family and as such take part in the activities and responsibilities in the family. The volunteer will have his/her three meals provided by the host family. Transport to and from home to the project is covered by the programme.
  
